title: The Intelligence - “Many, many more people turned out than would have been expected”—Georgia’s Senate races
summary:
Also on the daily podcast: finance looks at a quantum leap and the lingering influence of Confucianism in Korea“Many, many more people turned out than would have been expected”—Georgia’s Senate racesDEMOCRATS LOOK set to win both the run-off elections that will determine control of the Senate—and how President-elect Joe Biden will be able to govern.
Quantum computing is still nascent, its power yet to be truly tapped.
But the finance sector is already looking to squeeze it for analytical advantage.
And how Confucianism still influences society in South Korea.
